feat: establish testing infrastructure with Testcontainers and JaCoCo

Phase 1 implementation of optimized testing strategy:

1. **Parent pom.xml updates**:
   - Add Testcontainers BOM 1.19.3 to dependencyManagement
   - Configure JaCoCo plugin with exclusions for:
     - Constants classes (*Constants.class)
     - Configuration classes (*Configuration.class, *Config.class)
     - Simple DTOs/VOs (entrypoint/dto/**, entrypoint/vo/**)
     - Auto-configuration classes (autoconfiguration/**)

2. **file-srv-core test infrastructure**:
   - Add test dependencies: Testcontainers PostgreSQL, H2
   - Create BaseUnitTest.java: base class for fast unit tests
   - Create BaseIntegrationTest.java: base class for module integration tests
     - Uses @SpringBootTest with Testcontainers PostgreSQL
     - Configures @Transactional for automatic rollback
     - Supports real database testing with test data isolation

3. **file-srv-test module configuration**:
   - Add spring-boot-starter-web and test dependencies
   - Create IntegrationTestApplication.java: test-only Spring Boot app
   - Create ApplicationIntegrationTestBase.java:
     - Base class for application-level integration tests
     - Provides MockMvc for HTTP endpoint testing
     - Uses Testcontainers for real database
     - Supports full request-response cycle testing

4. **Documentation**:
   - Create docs/testing-strategy.md with:
     - Three-layer test architecture (unit/module/app integration)
     - Coverage targets (common 60%, core 80%, adapters 70%)
     - Given-When-Then pattern examples
     - Test data factory patterns
     - Mock usage guidelines
     - Test execution commands

Testing strategy follows best practices:
- Unit tests: fast, isolated, no Spring context
- Module integration tests: test component collaboration within module
- Application integration tests: verify end-to-end HTTP workflows
- All tests use Testcontainers for real PostgreSQL testing
- JaCoCo excludes noise from coverage reports

Ready for Phase 2: implementing actual test cases.
